# Next.js API Conventions

- Require authenticated user checks at the start of each route handler.
- Resolve tenant context before data queries and enforce tenant filters on read/write operations.
- Return JSON error objects with stable `code` and user-actionable `message`.
- Keep external API calls server-side and include health-check endpoints for integration diagnostics.
- Use explicit input validation for required fields and URL formats before database writes.
